05/11/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- EU finance and economy ministers Tuesday (4 November) approved Bulgaria's pre-accession economic programme. Finance Minister Milen Velchev represented Bulgaria at the meeting where Union representatives praised the government's achievements, including high economic growth rate, low inflation and budget deficit in 2002, as well as efforts to further reduce the country's external debt.
In other news, Solomon Passy launched an historic trip to Scotland on Tuesday, becoming the first Bulgarian foreign minister to visit there. (Dnevnik, Trud - 05/11/03; BTA, BNT, bTV - 04/11/03)
